{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "However, Mesboua et al. [86] observed a slight decrease in compressive strength with increasing bentonite content, suggesting that excessive amounts could negatively impact strength.",
    "In contrast, Akbar et al. [87] noted a 10% increase in compressive strength at 56 days with a 20% replacement level, indicating that higher bentonite content can still provide strength benefits under certain conditions.",
    "ZeoliteMadhuri et al. [88] found that while compressive strength initially decreased, it improved by 10-15% at 56 days with a 30% replacement level.",
    "Tran et al. [90] and Samimi et al.",
    "[91] reported similar strength gains at lower replacement levels (10-15%), indicating that moderate amounts of zeolite can effectively improve both compressive and flexural strength."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
